14/12/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A heroin stash worth 600,000 euros was seized on Friday (December 12th) at the Kalotina checkpoint on the border between Bulgaria and Serbia.
The drugs were found during a routine check of a vehicle with Turkish plates, the Bulgarian police announced.
It was destined for the markets of Western Europe and was distributed in 21 packages in special compartments in the car.
The amount totalled 13.5kg.
(Darik, Dir.bg, Netinfo, Dnevnik - 12/12/08)
